      "content=\"Virat Kohli is a renowned Indian international cricketer who is widely regarded as one of the greatest batsmen of all time. He is the current captain of the Indian national team and has been instrumental in the team's success in various formats of the game.\\n\\n**Early Life and Career**\\n\\nVirat Kohli was born on November 5, 1988, in Delhi, India. He began playing cricket at a young age and quickly rose through the ranks, representing Delhi in various age-group tournaments. Kohli made his first-class debut for Delhi in 2006 and soon caught the attention of national selectors.\\n\\n**International Career**\\n\\nKohli made his international debut for India in 2008, playing in a One-Day International (ODI) match against Sri Lanka. He quickly established himself as a key player in the Indian team, scoring his first ODI century in 2009. Kohli made his Test debut in 2011 and has since become one of the most successful Test batsmen of all time.\\n\\n**Achievements and Records**\\n\\nVirat Kohli has numerous records and achievements to his name, including:\\n\\n1. **Fastest to 10,000 ODI runs**: Kohli achieved this milestone in just 205 innings, surpassing Sachin Tendulkar's record.\\n2. **Most ODI centuries**: Kohli has scored 46 ODI centuries, the most by any Indian batsman.\\n3. **Most Test centuries as captain**: Kohli has scored 20 Test centuries as captain, the most by any Indian captain.\\n4. **ICC Cricketer of the Year**: Kohli has won the ICC Cricketer of the Year award twice (2017 and 2018).\\n5. **Padma Shri**: Kohli was awarded the Padma Shri, India's fourth-highest civilian honor, in 2017.\\n\\n**Captaincy and Leadership**\\n\\nKohli was appointed as the captain of the Indian team in 2014, succeeding Mahendra Singh Dhoni. Under his leadership, India has won numerous series and tournaments, including the 2016 ICC World Twenty20 and the 2018 Asia Cup. Kohli is known for his aggressive and passionate leadership style, which has inspired his teammates and helped India become one of the dominant teams in world cricket.\\n\\n**Personal Life**\\n\\nKohli is married to actress Anushka Sharma, and the couple has a daughter, Vamika. He is known for his fitness and wellness regime, and has been involved in various philanthropic activities, including supporting children's education and healthcare initiatives.\\n\\nOverall, Virat Kohli is a highly skilled and dedicated cricketer who has achieved immense success and recognition in the sport. He continues to be a role model and inspiration for millions of cricket fans around the world.\" response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 571, 'prompt_tokens': 42, 'total_tokens': 613, 'completion_time': 1.425924853, 'prompt_time': 0.010858281, 'queue_time': 0.049981179, 'total_time': 1.4367831340000001}, 'model_name': 'llama-3.3-70b-versatile', 'system_fingerprint': 'fp_2ddfbb0da0', 'finish_reason': 'stop', 'logprobs': None} id='run-58d4f5c3-17d0-4067-8c6e-485935a44f4f-0' usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 42, 'output_tokens': 571, 'total_tokens': 613}\n"
